A good deal was written about the sheep-wolf-dog trinity, how most men are sheep and evil men are wolves and the world needs more sheepdogs, "tamed wolves", to protect the sheep from the wolves. But a llama is more like a sheep and more effective at protecting a flock than a dog.

The llama is a herbivore that still terrifies carnivorous predators, is brutally loyal and intelligent, protective of other species, fearless, aggressive, it determines its own destiny through sheer willpower beyond any established categories. The divine South American creature.
